TY  - JOUR
T1  - Monoextremal Representations of a Class of Minimax Problems
AU  - Canon, M. D.
Y1  - 1969/01/01
PY  - 1969
DA  - 1969/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.15.5.228
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.15.5.228
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 228
EP  - 238
VL  - 15
IS  - 5
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - It is shown that minimax problems with convex-concave payoff and convex inequality constraints can be reduced to solving an equivalent constrained minimization problem. The objective function of the minimization problem is not convex, nor is the set of feasible solutions convex. Nevertheless, it is shown that any point which satisfies the first order necessary conditions for optimality must be a global minimum.
AB  - It is shown that minimax problems with convex-concave payoff and convex inequality constraints can be reduced to solving an equivalent constrained minimization problem. The objective function of the minimization problem is not convex, nor is the set of feasible solutions convex. Nevertheless, it is shown that any point which satisfies the first order necessary conditions for optimality must be a global minimum.
