TY  - JOUR
T1  - Optimal Continuous Review Policies for Two Product Inventory Systems with Joint Setup Costs
AU  - Ignall, Edward
Y1  - 1969/01/01
PY  - 1969
DA  - 1969/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.15.5.278
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.15.5.278
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 278
EP  - 283
VL  - 15
IS  - 5
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Minimum average cost ordering policies for continuously reviewed two product inventory systems with joint setup costs are sought. Disappointly, the optimal policy, even in a simple symmetric case, is not always simple: For some values of cost and demand parameters, a policy that would be difficult to implement is optimal. Markov Renewal Programming is used to find the region in parameter space where a given policy is optimal.
AB  - Minimum average cost ordering policies for continuously reviewed two product inventory systems with joint setup costs are sought. Disappointly, the optimal policy, even in a simple symmetric case, is not always simple: For some values of cost and demand parameters, a policy that would be difficult to implement is optimal. Markov Renewal Programming is used to find the region in parameter space where a given policy is optimal.
